:— 
<taxonomicName box="[471,711,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cardenasiae">
<emphasis box="[471,711,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia cardenasiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known only from one population inside the Yanachaga Chemillen National Park and thus should be considered as Data Deficient (DD) under IUCN criteria (2001). Based on its restricted distribution and habitat, following IUCN criteria (2001) as implemented in the IUCN guidelines (2011) we recommend that this species is considered Critically Endangered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="129" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,446,2092]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,315,1489,1515]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[351,588,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cardenasiae">
<emphasis box="[351,588,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia cardenasiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the short, stout petioles, glabrous leaves, and presence of pocket domatia. 
<taxonomicName box="[359,598,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cardenasiae">
<emphasis box="[359,598,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia cardenasiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="MacBride (1929: 184)" authorityName="MacBride" authorityPageNumber="184" authorityYear="1929" box="[818,1299,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="opacifolia">
<emphasis box="[818,1035,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia opacifolia</emphasis>
MacBride (1929: 184)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Naudin (1850: 228)" authorityName="Naudin" authorityPageNumber="228" authorityYear="1850" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cremophylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia cremophylla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Naudin, C. V." box="[284,511,1562,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="83 - 246" refId="ref9577" refString="Naudin, C. V. (1850) Melastomacearum monographicae descriptiones. [series 3] Annales des Sciences Naturelles; Botanique 16: 83 - 246." type="journal article" year="1850">Naudin (1850: 228)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacBride" authorityYear="1929" box="[524,740,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="opacifolia">
<emphasis box="[524,740,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia opacifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has completely sessile leaves, while 
<taxonomicName box="[1166,1341,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cardenasiae">
<emphasis box="[1166,1341,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">M. cardenasiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short (&lt;
<quantity box="[169,227,1598,1624]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
) petioles. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" box="[344,585,1598,1624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cremophylla">
<emphasis box="[344,585,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia cremophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has similar leaf morphology, though the petioles are longer, and it lacks any pocket domatia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,446,2092]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">
Foliar mite domatia (acarodomatia) are not uncommon among tropical 
<taxonomicName box="[1029,1223,1670,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Melastomataceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Goldenberg, R." box="[1245,1447,1670,1696]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" refId="ref8628" refString="Goldenberg, R. (2000) O Genero Miconia Ruiz &amp; Pav. (Melastomataceae): I. Listagens analiticas, II. Revisao Taxonomica da Secao Hypoxanthus (Rich. ex DC.) Hook. F. Ph. D. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Estadual de Campinas, Campinas, 249 pp." type="book" year="2000">Goldenberg 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F." box="[136,294,1706,1732]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="164 - 338" refId="ref8160" refString="Almeda, F. (2009) Melastomataceae. In: Davidse, G., Sousa S, M., Knapp, S. &amp; Chiang, F. (Eds.) Flora Mesoamericana. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico City, pp. 164 - 338." type="book chapter" year="2009">Almeda 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Larcher, L. &amp; Boeger, M. R. &amp; Flores, A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[308,534,1706,1732]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref8996" refString="Larcher, L., Boeger, M. R., Flores, A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2012) Morfologia das domacias foliares de Miconia sellowiana Naudin (Melastomataceae). Biotemas 25: 1 - 9. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5007 / 2175 - 7925.2012 v 25 n 1 p 1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Larcher 
<emphasis box="[405,465,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
), but unlike ant domatia (
<bibRefCitation author="Michelangeli, F. A." box="[835,1055,1706,1732]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="407 - 447" refId="ref9296" refString="Michelangeli, F. A. (2010) An annotated list and key of neotropical myrmecophilous Melastomataceae. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 61: 407 - 447." type="journal article" year="2010">Michelangeli 2010</bibRefCitation>
), have not been well documented, not even for other tropical plant families (
<bibRefCitation author="Romero, G. Q. &amp; Benson, W. W." box="[619,904,1742,1768]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="609 - 616" refId="ref9745" refString="Romero, G. Q. &amp; Benson, W. W. (2004) Leaf domatia mediate mutualism between mites and a tropical tree. Oecologia (Berlin) 140: 609 - 616. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00442 - 004 - 1626 - z" type="journal article" year="2004">Romero &amp; Benson 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Foliar pocket domatia may provide shelter for beneficial mites that eat fungal spores; alternatively they may provide shelter for mite predators that help control insect or arthropod herbivory (
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F." box="[485,643,1814,1840]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="137 - 150" refId="ref8131" refString="Almeda, F. (1989) Five New Berry-Fruited Species of Tropical American Melastomataceae. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 46: 137 - 150." type="journal article" year="1989">Almeda 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Romero, G. Q. &amp; Benson, W. W." box="[656,939,1814,1840]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="609 - 616" refId="ref9745" refString="Romero, G. Q. &amp; Benson, W. W. (2004) Leaf domatia mediate mutualism between mites and a tropical tree. Oecologia (Berlin) 140: 609 - 616. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00442 - 004 - 1626 - z" type="journal article" year="2004">Romero &amp; Benson 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Within 
<taxonomicName box="[1044,1162,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Miconieae">Miconieae</taxonomicName>
, acarodomatia have been observed in a broad span of geographical and ecological zones, from Andean tropical montane forest (
<emphasis box="[1302,1335,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">e.g</emphasis>
., 
<taxonomicName authority="Gleason (1933: 43)" authorityName="Gleason" authorityPageNumber="43" authorityYear="1933" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cookii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia cookii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gleason, H. A." box="[212,428,1886,1912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="41 - 48" refId="ref8570" refString="Gleason, H. A. (1933) Nine South American Melastomes. Phytologia 1: 41 - 48." type="journal article" year="1933">Gleason (1933: 43)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Desrousseaux 1797: 55) Naudin (1850: 245)" authorityName="Naudin" authorityPageNumber="245" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Desrousseaux" baseAuthorityPageNumber="55" baseAuthorityYear="1797" box="[442,1133,1886,1913]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crocea">
<emphasis box="[442,617,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia crocea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Desrousseaux, M." box="[634,896,1886,1913]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="31 - 57" refId="ref8455" refString="Desrousseaux, M. (1797) Melastome. In: Lamarck, B. D. (Ed.) Encyclopedie Agasse, Paris, pp. 31 - 57." type="book chapter" year="1797">Desrousseaux 1797: 55</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Naudin, C. V." box="[912,1133,1886,1913]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="83 - 246" refId="ref9577" refString="Naudin, C. V. (1850) Melastomacearum monographicae descriptiones. [series 3] Annales des Sciences Naturelles; Botanique 16: 83 - 246." type="journal article" year="1850">Naudin (1850: 245)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Don 1823: 313) Naudin (1850: 244))" authorityName="Naudin" authorityPageNumber="244" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Don" baseAuthorityPageNumber="313" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis box="[1147,1315,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia media</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Don, D." pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="276 - 329" refId="ref8487" refString="Don, D. (1823) An illustration of the natural family of plants called Melastomaceae. Memoirs of the Wernerian Natural History Society 4: 276 - 329." type="journal article" year="1823">Don 1823: 313</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Naudin, C. V." box="[195,430,1922,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="83 - 246" refId="ref9577" refString="Naudin, C. V. (1850) Melastomacearum monographicae descriptiones. [series 3] Annales des Sciences Naturelles; Botanique 16: 83 - 246." type="journal article" year="1850">Naudin (1850: 244))</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, Brazilian cerrado (
<emphasis box="[655,688,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">e.g</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="(de Candolle 1828: 194) Naudin (1850: 171)" authorityName="Naudin" authorityPageNumber="171" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="de Candolle" baseAuthorityPageNumber="194" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[703,1445,1922,1949]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pusilliflora">
<emphasis box="[703,929,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia pusilliflora</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="de Candolle, A. P." box="[945,1205,1922,1948]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" refId="ref8429" refString="de Candolle, A. P. (1828) Memoires sur la famille des Melastomacees. Treuttel et Wurtz, Paris, 82 pp." type="book" year="1828">de Candolle 1828: 194</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Naudin, C. V." box="[1221,1445,1922,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="83 - 246" refId="ref9577" refString="Naudin, C. V. (1850) Melastomacearum monographicae descriptiones. [series 3] Annales des Sciences Naturelles; Botanique 16: 83 - 246." type="journal article" year="1850">Naudin (1850: 171)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Naudin (1850: 206))" authorityName="Naudin" authorityPageNumber="206" authorityYear="1850" box="[136,601,1958,1985]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sellowiana">
<emphasis box="[136,358,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia sellowiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Naudin, C. V." box="[367,601,1958,1985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="83 - 246" refId="ref9577" refString="Naudin, C. V. (1850) Melastomacearum monographicae descriptiones. [series 3] Annales des Sciences Naturelles; Botanique 16: 83 - 246." type="journal article" year="1850">Naudin (1850: 206))</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, to Central American cloud forest (
<emphasis box="[1003,1036,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">e.g</emphasis>
., 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeda (1989: 140))" authorityName="Almeda" authorityPageNumber="140" authorityYear="1989" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="hammelii">
<emphasis box="[1058,1273,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Clidemia hammelii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F." pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="137 - 150" refId="ref8131" refString="Almeda, F. (1989) Five New Berry-Fruited Species of Tropical American Melastomataceae. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 46: 137 - 150." type="journal article" year="1989">Almeda (1989: 140))</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. These domatia are expressed as either foliar pockets or hair tufts at vein axils. Moreover, there appears to be an ecological variation in their occurrence (
<bibRefCitation author="Larcher, L. &amp; Boeger, M. R. &amp; Flores, A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[590,811,2030,2056]" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref8996" refString="Larcher, L., Boeger, M. R., Flores, A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2012) Morfologia das domacias foliares de Miconia sellowiana Naudin (Melastomataceae). Biotemas 25: 1 - 9. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5007 / 2175 - 7925.2012 v 25 n 1 p 1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Larcher 
<emphasis box="[686,743,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName box="[860,1096,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cardenasiae">
<emphasis box="[860,1096,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Miconia cardenasiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not all leaves on our specimen produce foliar pockets. This variation among leaves on a species bearing acarodomatia is not uncommon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
